"Teixeira C.E., Torves J.C., Finotti A.R., Fedrizzi F., Marinho F.A.M., Teixeira P.F.","Studies on the aerobic methane oxidation at three sanitary landfills covers in Brazil [Estudos sobre a oxidação aeróbia do metano na cobertura de três aterros sanitários no Brasil]",2009,"Engenharia Sanitaria e Ambiental","14","1",,"99","108",,,,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-66249138505&partnerID=40&md5=f23aa2a1c27e7b423d6b471152c50914","Departamento de Engenharia Química, Pesquisadora do Instituto de Saneamento Ambiental, Universidade de Caxias do Sul (UCS), Brazil; Biotecnologia pela UCS; Departamento de Engenharia Química, Instituto de Saneamento Ambiental da UCS; Engenharia Ambiental da UCS; Escola Politécnica Universidade de São Paulo (EPUSP), Brazil; EPUSP, Brazil","Teixeira, C.E., Departamento de Engenharia Química, Pesquisadora do Instituto de Saneamento Ambiental, Universidade de Caxias do Sul (UCS), Brazil; Torves, J.C., Biotecnologia pela UCS; Finotti, A.R., Departamento de Engenharia Química, Instituto de Saneamento Ambiental da UCS; Fedrizzi, F., Engenharia Ambiental da UCS; Marinho, F.A.M., Escola Politécnica Universidade de São Paulo (EPUSP), Brazil; Teixeira, P.F., EPUSP, Brazil","The biological and aerobic oxidation of methane within the soil cover of municipal solid waste landfills is one an alternative to minimize emissions of greenhouse effect gases. This study aims at assess the biological oxidation of methane within the final cover of three landfills in Brazil (two municipal ones and one experimental cell). The soil samples obtained from the landfill cover were characterized by geotechnical and microbiological tests. In the laboratory the consumption of methane from each sample were evaluated. The results revealed the presence of methanotrophic bacteria and consumption of methane in the laboratory was observed, which also suggest that there is an inverse relation between the degree of saturation at the time of sampling and the number of methanotrophic bacteria.","Global warming; Greenhouse effect; Landfill cover; Methane; Methane oxidation; Methanotrophic bacteria; Sanitary landfill; Solid waste","Bacteria (microorganisms)",,,,,,"(1984) NBR 6459, Solo - Determinação do limite de liquidez, , ASSOCIAÇÃO BRASILEIRA DE NORMAS TÉCNICAS. Rio de Janeiro; (1984) NBR 6508, Massa específica - Grãos de solo que passam na peneira de 4,8 mm: Determinação da massa especifica, , ASSOCIAÇÃO BRASILEIRA DE NORMAS TÉCNICAS. Rio de Janeiro; (1984) NBR 7180, Solo - Determinação do limite de plasticidade, , ASSOCIAÇÃO BRASILEIRA DE NORMAS TÉCNICAS. Rio de Janeiro; (1984) NBR 7181, Solo - Análise Granulométrica, , ASSOCIAÇÃO BRASILEIRA DE NORMAS TÉCNICAS. Rio de Janeiro; Barlaz, M.A., Evaluation of a biologically active cover for mitigation of landfill gas emissions (2004) Environmental Science & Technology, 38 (18), pp. 4891-4899. , set; Bender, M., Conrad, R., Effect of CH4 concentrations and soil conditions on the induction of CH4 oxidation activity (1995) Soil Biology & Biochemistry, 27 (12), pp. 1517-1527. , dez; Boeckx, P., van Cleemput, O., Villaralvo, I., Methane emission from a landfill and the methane oxidising capacity of its covering soil (1996) Soil Biology & Biochemistry, 28 (10-11), pp. 1397-1405. , out./nov; Bogner, J., Landfills as Atmospheric Methane Sources and Sinks (1995) Chemosphere, 31 (9), pp. 4119-30. , nov; Börjesson, G., Svensson, B.H., Seasonal and diurnal methane emissions from a landfill and their Regulation by methane oxidation (1997) Waste Management and Research, 15 (1), pp. 33-54. , fev; Christophersen, M., Lateral gas transport in soil adjacent to an old landfill: Factors governing emissions and methane oxidation (2001) Waste Management and Research, 19, pp. 126-143; Dedysh, S.N., Panikov, N., Tiedje, J.M., Acidophilic Methanotrophic communities from Sphagnum Peat Bogs (1998) Applied and Environmental Microbiology, 64, pp. 922-929. , mar; Einola, J.-K.M., Karhu, A.E., Rintala, J.A., Me